TRANSLA TIONS.

ROMEO.

O MY love! my wife! Death‚ that hath suck’d the honey of thy breath, Hath had no power yet upon thy beauty: Thou art not conquer’d ; beauty's ensign yet Is crimson in thy lips and in thy cheeks‚ And death’s pale flag is not advanced there. ’ Tybalt, liestthou there in thy bloody sheet? O, what more favour can I do to thee, Than with that hand that cut thy youth in twain

To sunder his that was thine enemy?
